<div id="review_4138969450" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4138969450" />
    <a title="Amber J" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/66639925-amber-j"><img alt="Amber J" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1638816728p2/66639925.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4138969450?book_show_action=true">Sep 13, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amber J" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amber J" href="/user/show/66639925-amber-j">Amber J</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/66639925-amber-j?shelf=2021-reading-challenge">2021-reading-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4138969450" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5146312538199065611">I started this book by reading the physical version. I didn&apos;t get very far and I even marked it as DNF. But then I decided to give it a go with the audio. That wasn&apos;t as bad and the narrator is the same one who narrates the Guild Hunter series. So that is kinda cool.<br/><br/>I don&apos;t understand this Luce. Why would anyone want to see their past selves die, over and over again? I don&apos;t know what she was trying to accomplish and all the times where she could have messed up her past so bad, and she didn&apos;t ev</span>
  <span id="freeText5146312538199065611" style="display:none">I started this book by reading the physical version. I didn't get very far and I even marked it as DNF. But then I decided to give it a go with the audio. That wasn't as bad and the narrator is the same one who narrates the Guild Hunter series. So that is kinda cool.<br /><br />I don't understand this Luce. Why would anyone want to see their past selves die, over and over again? I don't know what she was trying to accomplish and all the times where she could have messed up her past so bad, and she didn't even think twice? Honestly, I think Luce is just not the brightest.<br /><br />Daniel, I still don't understand why he feels the need to keep so much from her. Maybe, some of it he can't tell, but keeping so much extra secret would leave anyone feeling frustrated and lied to. No...just way too much unnecessary drama going on. <br /><br /><br />How I choose my rating:<br />1* Didn't like it at all. These are rare as I usually just don't finish any book I dislike this much.<br />2** Didn't like it. Again usually DNF if I dislike it this much, but occasionally I feel it still has potential and I try to stick with it to the end.<br />3*** I liked it. It wasn't great but it was enjoyable enough. It is unlikely I'll ever reread it but I might finish the series if it is a part of one.<br />4**** I really liked this book. Maybe not a work of genius, but highly entertaining. I might reread this at some point, and I will almost always finish the series if part of one.<br />5***** I loved this book. I found little to no issues with it at all. I will probably reread this and possibly more than once. I will definitely finish the series if it's part of one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5146312538199065611" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


